programmingWithoutVariables:
In C, you must declare every variable's type upfront:
```c
int age = 25;
char name[50] = "Alice";
float score = 98.5;
// age = "hello";  // COMPILE ERROR — can't store string in int variable
```
In Java:
```java
int age = 25;
String name = "Alice";
// age = "hello";  // COMPILE ERROR
```
Python removes this entire category of friction — the type is inferred at runtime from the value itself.

